reviews.review_text:
Sometimes we are so stubborn..... ....As dead heads. I generally ignored anything past the early eighties in terms of my personal collection or recorded shows. I am a 70's guy, but some of these songs are as tight as you will ever see them. FANTASTIC Foolish Heart, great song. Since Jerry's death I am giving all era's a close listen, its all we have left of the old man. They worked so hard for us, and it is clear we were most important after the music. They pushed harder than any band. To this day, I still feel like I lost a big brother or spiritual leader. This site gives me joy every day of my life, and gave me a wealth of my drug of choice, Grateful Dead music. 
     Peace to all, and if there is a heaven, Jerry is already jamming with Brent, Keith, Pig and the rest of our brothers and sisters in the great gig in the sky. He's playing with ten fingers too!
fast hard playing check out shakedown

Awesome show. This show was incredible. The did the second half of a Dark Star that from the first night. into miracle. when the band let us sing "i need a miracle everyday" The lighting guys lit the whole crowd up it was definitely a highlight of the whole tour for me. The band was red hot for the whole fall tour into these New Years lead up shows. I am so Grateful that these shows are on here to take me back to those days. I sure would hate to see Archive go away. Thanks guys for this incredible resource!

Great set list GOGD Love the set list that dark star to book end the show is so killer so creative the he’s gone jam is good and the shakedown jams hard. Vinny seems to be on his own and kills it I think.
